nodes.title: Sampler Step and CFG
widgets_values:
Sampler Steps: Total Number of steps for ksampler. (Default value - 26) 

Sampler CFG - Use Between 5 - 9, Higher values causes artifacts, color noise, and weird backgrounds. Default value is 8. 
Use Lower 5-7 for Realistic Models and 7-9 for anime/cartoon.

nodes.title: AnimateDiff
widgets_values:
Model - motionModel_v01 and Temporaldiff-v1-animatediff was seen to produce best results.

----------------------------
motionModel_v01 - https://civitai.com/models/139237?modelVersionId=154097

Temporaldiff - https://huggingface.co/CiaraRowles/TemporalDiff/tree/main
* Temporal Diff can sometime give yellow tint to the final image, which can be fixed in post using curves>playing with the blue channel.


Feel free to test out other motion models.

nodes.title: Overall Adjustment
widgets_values:
Play with Brightness, Saturation, Contrast, Gamma for adjustments

Play with RGB values to create some unique light maps.

nodes.title: Subject Adjustment
widgets_values:
Control the intensity of Light on the subject with this node

1) Brightness: if your Character is too dim or overexposed you can counter it here.  

2) Saturation: You can desaturate or oversaturate to make the matching the colors with the light map more accurate.

nodes.title: Light Map On Top
widgets_values:
When True: Light Maps will be on top of the subject and more dominant 


When False: Subject will be on top and more dominant and Brighter.

nodes.title: IC Light Setup
widgets_values:
1) Unmute Single or Sequence According to your need and connect the reroute node to the "Pick One Input" 

*Make Sure when using the sequence, the number of images in the folder is same or greater than the number images of Controlnet folder.

nodes.title: File Name + Special Feature
widgets_values: #002 - IC Light Changer - No LCM - All in One

nodes.title: Light ControlNet
widgets_values:
1) Strength: Use value between 0.2 - 0.5 

Stronger Strength will cause over exposed image. 

2) End Percent: Use value between 0.35 - 0.6

High Values will have a sharp border transition

nodes.title: HigheRes Fix | Detail Enhancer | AD Macro Motion
widgets_values:
Inject Additional Refiner Noise - Use value 0 - 1 (It enhances the minute details, use with add details lora)

Refiner Upscale - It upscales the image - (value around 1.2 - 1.6 is good, above 1.6 no change is observed)
(Default Value - 1.2 which is good)
--------------------------------------------
*Start Refiner from nth step: It's an alternative to Denoising Technique, which mimics the denoiser. Default is 20. 

Refiner from nth Step Theory:
 
For Total Sampler Steps of 10 - 

Value 1 will mean denoise value 1.0
Value 5 will mean denoise value 0.5
Value 10 will mean denoise value 0

and like so, it is dependent on sampler steps. Lower Values means high denoise which will change elements. 


----------------------------------------------


Detail Enhancer - It injects noise in the model, use up to max value of 20 - Higer values cause micro details into morphing/sliding. (Default value is 2) 

AD Macro Motion - AnimateDiff motion of Background Elements is controlled by this value. Use up to max value of 10. Higer values cause jittering/Choppy motion. Min value 1 is for normal motion (Default Value - 3 for stable elements, almost no motion)

*Higer value above 10 till 1000 in AD Macro Motion gives ghosting like Echo images, can be cool for some abstract effects. Sometimes it becomes like deforum img2img animation with consistent jittering background. Try different values for fun. 

*Higer Values than 10 till 200 in macro motion can sometimes experimentally give perfectly still background with good details and good character consistency, you need to find your x value.

nodes.title: CheckPoint and Lora
widgets_values:
* Use Realistic Models for Realistic Results

* Use Cartoon or Anime Models for Stylistic Results and for Fun

* Loras works as usual just use on low strength 0.9 max, Some Artifacts/ Over Detailing 
 is seen on full strength.

nodes.title: Custom Save Location
widgets_values:
1) Unmute the Change Output Path Node
2) Enter your Preferred Save location

By default, the Videos are saved in 

Comfyui > output

nodes.title: Source Video
widgets_values:
Use Frame Load Cap of 10 for testing first. 
Then 0 to render all frames.

nodes.title: Fit Size Limiter
widgets_values:
By default, it will be 2048 that means max resolution is capped to 2048 pixels

 
If you write 1024 in max size, then images will downscale and fit inside that size automatically

nodes.title: Upscale for Face Fix
widgets_values:
If your faces are still not satisfactory after face fix with 0.35 denoise

then you can upscale the Images beforehand so it more resolution to work on hence, good faces

Default value = 1.2
Use max value = 2.0

nodes.title: Denoise
widgets_values:
Use Denoise value upto 0.45.

Above this value, faces will have incorrect positions and angle 

Then you can use the Upscale for Face Fix Node

nodes.title: #3 AnimateDiff IC Light Changer v4.0 - Video2Video
widgets_values:
HOW TO USE: 



1) Upload Source Video.
2) Upload Light Map Video or Single Light Map Image.
3) Enter Load Cap and other Settings, same settings should be in Light Map Video. 
4) Enter Prompts for more lights Map used like Sunlight or neon lights.  
5) Loras work as usual (Some of not compatible with animatediff, test it first with 10 frames)
6) Change Light Map Properties
7) Hit render

Outputs will be saved in Comfyui > Outputs 

*Caution: Don't Use Lora on full strength.

nodes.title: IC Image Condition Settings [Optional]
widgets_values:
Pretend that this IC light controlnet is a tile controlnet but without light data and color data.


These adjustments are NOT effective in controlling the light or color data, just for controlling brightness, contrast, gamma of the conditioning to some extent. 

Leave these settings to default. Not important.

nodes.title: Remap Range [Optional]
widgets_values:
Use this node to control the contrast of the Conditioning. 

Higher min value and Lower Max values can make some details disappear. 

can be effective if you see some burning in the renders, to calm down the conditioning.

nodes.title: Affecting Area
widgets_values:
Use Blend mode 

1) Multiple: to have the character to be dominant in the shadow region. 

2) Screen: to have the character to be dominant in the shadow region. 

3) Blend factor works like Opacity

nodes.title: IC Sampler Steps
widgets_values:
For an End step of 20
Start Step at 
- 0 will have no Light map effect.
- 5 will have 50 percent effect
- 10 will have 100 percent effect.

Above 10 will produce messed up results 

So, about 3-8 is a good value to test from.


When Generate New Background is TRUE, you can go Lower than 5 for Better Results

nodes.title: IC Light Conditioning
widgets_values:
Use Value between 0.18 - 0.21 

Lower value will have calm effect. 
Higher value will have contrasting effect burning of pixels

nodes.title: Refiner Steps
widgets_values:
For an End step of 25
Start Step at 
- 10 and below will work like raw sampler and will give you morphing objects
- 15 will work like a proper refiner.
- 20 will not work properly


Above 20 and above will produce messed up results 

So, Default 16 is good.

nodes.title: Co Adaptor Depth Model
widgets_values:
https://huggingface.co/TencentARC/T2I-Adapter/blob/main/models/coadapter-depth-sd15v1.pth

Put in Comfyui > models > ControlNet

This Depth Model competitively gives better and stable results than the default depth CN model

nodes.title: Generate New Background
widgets_values:
When False: The background will be similar to the original but with new lighting Applied

When True: New Background will be generated according to the Depth ControlNet.

Also add background keywords in the prompts.

nodes.title: Positive
widgets_values: 1girl, sunlight, sunset, white shirt, black short jeans, interior, room

nodes.title: Remap Range
widgets_values:
Use this node to control the overall global brightness and Darkness the whole image.

1) Higher min value will brighten the scene

2) Lower Max values will make the Scene Darker and can convert the Brighter areas into morphing objects like the QrCode Monster CN


Use mostly the Min value to 0.1 or 0.2 to light up a scene a little bit. 

Min Value 0 will have a pitch-black shadow for black pixels of the light map.
